<subSubSection id="C31665703233FFD983E9FB402CCBFA22" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB336FB3233FFD983E9FB402F7CFB2E" blockId="12.[151,1436,1159,1509]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Monotypic genus represented by 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D783233FFD98177FB402EE1FB66" authorityName="Percequillo, Weksler &amp; Costa" authorityYear="2011" box="[521,714,1159,1185]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Drymoreomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="albimaculatus">
<emphasis id="B978EAE93233FFD98177FB402EE1FB66" box="[521,714,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">D. albimaculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF9D4B0A3233FFD981A9FB40284FFB66" author="Percequillo, A. R. &amp; Weksler, M. &amp; Costa, L. P." box="[727,1124,1159,1185]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="357 - 390" refId="ref71643" refString="Percequillo, A. R., Weksler, M. &amp; Costa, L. P. (2011) A new genus and species of rodent from the Brazilian Atlantic Forest (Rodentia: Cricetidae: Sigmodontinae: Oryzomyini), with comments on oryzomyine biogeography. Zoological Journal of Linnean Society, 161, 357 - 390. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.2010.00643. x" type="journal article" year="2011">
Percequillo, Weksler &amp; 
<collectingRegion id="49C8F8193233FFD9809DFB402808FB66" box="[995,1059,1159,1185]" country="New Zealand" name="West Coast" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Costa</collectingRegion>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
), all known specimens were from the eastern slopes of the Serra do Mar, in the coastal Brazilian Atlantic Rainforest from 
<collectingRegion id="49C8F8193233FFD987E2FB6C2917FB02" box="[1180,1340,1195,1221]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
to 
<collectingRegion id="49C8F8193233FFD98620FB6C2CDDFB2E" country="Brazil" name="Santa Catarina" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Santa Catarina</collectingRegion>
states (
<bibRefCitation id="EF9D4B0A3233FFD98234FB082E60FB2E" author="Percequillo, A. R. &amp; Weksler, M. &amp; Costa, L. P." box="[330,587,1231,1257]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="357 - 390" refId="ref71643" refString="Percequillo, A. R., Weksler, M. &amp; Costa, L. P. (2011) A new genus and species of rodent from the Brazilian Atlantic Forest (Rodentia: Cricetidae: Sigmodontinae: Oryzomyini), with comments on oryzomyine biogeography. Zoological Journal of Linnean Society, 161, 357 - 390. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.2010.00643. x" type="journal article" year="2011">
Percequillo 
<emphasis id="B978EAE93233FFD982ACFB082E28FB2E" box="[466,515,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">et al</emphasis>
. 2011
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9D4B0A3233FFD98129FB082F60FB2E" author="Delciellos, A. C. &amp; Aguieiras, M. &amp; Geise, L. &amp; Weksler, M. &amp; Rocha-Barbosa, O." box="[599,843,1230,1257]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="1572" refId="ref65957" refString="Delciellos, A. C., Aguieiras, M., Geise, L., Weksler, M. &amp; Rocha-Barbosa, O. (2015) First record of Drymoreomys albimaculatus Percequillo, Weksler &amp; Costa, 2011 (Rodentia, Cricetidae, Sigmodontinae) in Rio de Janeiro state, Brazil. Check List, 11 (2), 1572. https: // doi. org / 10.15560 / 11.2.1572" type="journal article" year="2015">
Delciellos 
<emphasis id="B978EAE93233FFD981B1FB082F2AFB2E" box="[719,769,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">et al</emphasis>
. 2015
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB336FB3233FFD983B9FB342CCBFA22" blockId="12.[151,1436,1159,1509]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Karyotype: 2n = 62 and FN = 62. Autosomal complement: one small metacentric pair, and 29 acrocentric pairs large to small decreasing in size. Sex chromosomes: X, a large submetacentric; Y, a large submetacentric slightly smaller than the X (
<bibRefCitation id="EF9D4B0A3233FFD98202FAFC2E8CFA92" author="Suarez-Villota, E. Y. &amp; Di-Nizo, C. B. &amp; Neves, C. L. &amp; Silva, M. J. J." box="[380,679,1339,1365]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="65 - 76" refId="ref74155" refString="Suarez-Villota, E. Y., Di-Nizo, C. B., Neves, C. L. &amp; Silva, M. J. J. (2013) First cytogenetic information for Drymoreomys albimaculatus (Rodentia, Cricetidae), a recently described genus from Brazilian Atlantic Forest. ZooKeys, 303, 65 - 76. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 303.4873" type="journal article" year="2013">
Suárez-Villota 
<emphasis id="B978EAE93233FFD98156FAFC2E77FA92" box="[552,604,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">et al</emphasis>
. 2013
</bibRefCitation>
, pp. 68, 
<figureCitation id="13372A7E3233FFD98072FAFC2F7BFA92" box="[780,848,1339,1365]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,1069,1943]" captionTargetId="figure-342@4.[159,1429,1062,1950]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Collection localities of Oryzomyini species analyzed in this work. (1) Claúdia, Mato Grosso state; (2) and (3) Rio Japurá, Amazonas state; (4) and (5) Rio Içá, Amazonas state." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423617" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4423617/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9D4B0A3233FFD9801EFAFC2870FA92" author="Delciellos, A. C. &amp; Aguieiras, M. &amp; Geise, L. &amp; Weksler, M. &amp; Rocha-Barbosa, O." box="[864,1115,1338,1365]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="1572" refId="ref65957" refString="Delciellos, A. C., Aguieiras, M., Geise, L., Weksler, M. &amp; Rocha-Barbosa, O. (2015) First record of Drymoreomys albimaculatus Percequillo, Weksler &amp; Costa, 2011 (Rodentia, Cricetidae, Sigmodontinae) in Rio de Janeiro state, Brazil. Check List, 11 (2), 1572. https: // doi. org / 10.15560 / 11.2.1572" type="journal article" year="2015">
Delciellos 
<emphasis id="B978EAE93233FFD980A5FAFC2825FA92" box="[987,1038,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">et al</emphasis>
. 2015
</bibRefCitation>
). C-banding metaphases exhibited pericentromeric constitutive heterochromatic blocks on all autosomes and on the long arm of Y. G-banding was also performed. FISH with telomeric sequences revealed signals at the ends of all chromosomes, and additional telomeric sequences were found on the pericentromeric region of both X and Y chromosomes (
<bibRefCitation id="EF9D4B0A3233FFD987C4FA602CFFFA22" author="Suarez-Villota, E. Y. &amp; Di-Nizo, C. B. &amp; Neves, C. L. &amp; Silva, M. J. J." pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="65 - 76" refId="ref74155" refString="Suarez-Villota, E. Y., Di-Nizo, C. B., Neves, C. L. &amp; Silva, M. J. J. (2013) First cytogenetic information for Drymoreomys albimaculatus (Rodentia, Cricetidae), a recently described genus from Brazilian Atlantic Forest. ZooKeys, 303, 65 - 76. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 303.4873" type="journal article" year="2013">
Suárez-Villota 
<emphasis id="B978EAE93233FFD9861AFA6029BEFA06" box="[1380,1429,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">et al</emphasis>
. 2013
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
